FBIS4-65899 "drweu101_q_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-101 Daily Report 25 May 1994 TURKEY Explosions Injure 2 at Istanbul Train Station Explosions Injure 2 at Istanbul Train Station TA2505053094 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 0430 GMT 25 May 94 TA2505053094 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network Turkish BFN [Text] Two people have been slightly injured after four [number as heard] concussion grenades [ses bombasi], set with a timing mechanism, exploded in Istanbul's Harem Station. The grenades, planted at the train station by unidentified persons, went off at short intervals beginning at approximately 2300 last night. Sevki Mustafaoglu was injured in the leg and taken to Haydarpasa Hospital, and Murat Yaman was treated on the scene. Officials stated that one of the concussion grenades was placed inside a telephone booth, one at a coffee shop, and another at the back entrance to a police station in the train station. An investigation is under way. Meanwhile, at around the same time, a Molotov cocktail was thrown at Sisli's Bag-Kur [Social Security Association for Tradesmen, Artisans, and Independent Workers] building. No one was injured in the incident.
